{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17568260","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17568260"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T00:12:17+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T00:12:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19714"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"19714","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/19714"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.34,0.06,0.21,0.25]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"12492"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112736"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"12492","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/12492"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19714"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94770"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4970"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"6409"},{"type":"tags","id":"6479"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"29955"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39818"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40143"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44661"},{"type":"contributions","id":"46336"},{"type":"contributions","id":"48048"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112736","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/112736"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 63-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with concerns about his penis. Over the past three months, he has noticed progressive curvature of his erect penis and pain during intercourse. He reports that the deformity is making sexual activity increasingly difficult but still possible. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Examination reveals a palpable plaque on the dorsal aspect of the penis with approximately 30 degrees of dorsal curvature when flaccid.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Oral tadalafil","Immediate surgical correction","Penile implant insertion","Watchful waiting alone","Topical corticosteroid cream"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with typical features of Peyronie\u0027s disease in the acute phase, characterised by progressive penile curvature, pain during erections, and a palpable plaque. The condition results from abnormal wound healing, leading to the formation of a fibrous plaque in the tunica albuginea.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral tadalafil\u003C/strong\u003E is the appropriate first-line treatment during the acute phase of Peyronie\u0027s disease. This phosphodiesterase type-5 (PDE5) inhibitor can reduce the collagen or smooth muscle and collagen III-I  in the Peyronie\u0027s disease-like plaque. It helps speed up the scar maturation process and is typically recommended for three to six months.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImmediate surgical correction\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate at this stage. Surgery is reserved for severe cases where penetrative intercourse is impossible due to the degree of curvature. Less than 10% of men with Peyronie\u0027s disease require surgical correction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPenile implant insertion\u003C/strong\u003E is indicated for patients who have both significant curvature and erectile dysfunction. This patient has not reported erectile dysfunction, only difficulty with intercourse due to curvature, making this option inappropriate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWatchful waiting alone\u003C/strong\u003E without any intervention is not optimal, given the progressive nature of the condition in its acute phase. However, many men eventually adopt a watchful waiting approach after initial treatment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETopical corticosteroid cream\u003C/strong\u003E has no proven efficacy in Peyronie\u0027s disease, as the plaque is located beneath the skin in the tunica albuginea, rendering topical treatments ineffective.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe management approach should be tailored to the phase of the disease, the degree of deformity, and the impact on sexual function. Patient counselling regarding the natural history of the condition and realistic treatment expectations is essential.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A phosphodiesterase type-5 inhibitor is the first-line oral therapy for Peyronie\u0027s disease to help speed scar maturation.","Most men with Peyronie\u0027s disease can be managed conservatively without surgical intervention."],"references":["Chung PH, Han TM, Rudnik B, Das AK. Peyronie\u2019s disease: what do we know and how do we treat it? Can J Urol 2020; 27(Suppl 3):11-19 Available at: https://www.canjurol.com/html/free-articles/Cdn_JU27-S3_06_DrChung_S.pdf","Love C, Katz DJ, Chung E, et al. Peyronie\u2019s disease \u2212 Watch out  for the bend. Aust Fam Phys 2017; 16. https://www.racgp.org.au/afp/2017/september/peyronies-disease","Tsambarlis P, Levine LA. Nonsurgical management of Peyronie\u2019s disease. Nat Rev Urol. 2019; 16:172-86.","Chung E, DeYoung L, Brock GB. The Role of PDE5 Inhibitors in Penile Septal Scar Remodeling:  Assessment of Clinical and Radiological Outcomesjsm_22171472. J Sex Med. 2011; 8:1472-477."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94770"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19714"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21694"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21694","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21694"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/tFufEh0vaWpvrJ9WG8EvNt3xU34oOW.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/tFufEh0vaWpvrJ9WG8EvNt3xU34oOW.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1024,"height":768}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94770","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/94770"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-04T20:26:51+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-04T20:27:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"12492"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112736"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"36","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/36"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd43","name":"Urology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"ht